{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Recommended: Relational Core + JSONB Config\n      Binders and tabs are relational tables (proper FKs, RLS). But each tab has a JSONB config column for flexible metadata (icon, color, custom fields). Templates stored as a separate binder_templates table with a JSONB structure column that snapshots the tab layout.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Best of both: relational integrity + flexibility\n            RLS works naturally on binder/tab level\n            Templates are clean JSONB snapshots\n            Easy to extend without schema changes\n            Matches your existing patterns (relational + config)\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Slightly more tables than option B\n            Need to keep JSONB config and relational data in sync","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1775486756845}
